Deprecated Methods
com.intersys.classes.ObjectHandle._close()
          To close object myObject Use Database.closeObject(myObject.getZRef()) instead. This method does not exactly what can be expected from it, because it closes and makes invalid all instances of objects which refer to particular object reference. Therefore it's use is dangerous. 
com.intersys.classes.CacheRootObject._close()
          To close object myObject Use Database.closeObject(myObject.getOref()) instead. This method does not exactly what can be expected from it, because it closes and makes invalid all instances of objects which refer to particular object reference. Therefore it's use is dangerous. 
com.intersys.classes.RegisteredObject._constructClone()
          Please use instance method constructClone () instead. 
com.intersys.classes.RegisteredObject._constructClone(Database, RegisteredObject)
          Please use instance method constructClone () instead. 
com.intersys.classes.RegisteredObject._constructClone(Database, RegisteredObject, Boolean, StringHolder)
          Please use instance method constructClone (boolean deep, StringHolder cloned) instead.
